**Overall Meaning:**

This verse highlights the importance of meditating on Krishna in Mathura. It states that those who meditate on Krishna specifically in Mathura, with the eight-petaled lotus of the heart blooming within them, achieve liberation. It emphasizes the special significance of Mathura and the transformative power of devotion to Krishna. 
